						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Dhvajastaṁbha in the Muktēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra—A.D. 1288.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in Sanskrit verse is very badly damaged. It belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandradēva</hi> and is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1210, Sarvadhāri, Śrāvaṇa s11u. 5, Monday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1288, July 5, Monday.</hi> It seems to refer to the erection of a <hi rend="italic">Kīrtistaṁbha</hi> by <hi rend="italic">Sainyādhipati</hi> <hi rend="bold">[Sāḷiva].</hi></p>						

						</summary>
